review_blob:
Nice color of honey and apple cider. Not much head at all. Aroma of pumpkin, honey, and spice. Nice balanced taste of the same with a hint of orange. Satisfies late summer thirst without being too light or heavy. Drank cold out of the fridge in a room temperature mug. Definitely adding this to my list of New Belgium favorites. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob:
Has a nice fall amber color. Aroma seemed faint. A bit too much carbonation; tasted slightly like seltzer water mixed with beer. To be fair, it could have been a bad bottle in the singles craft beer section at the grocery store I bought it from. It happens. I'd try a couple more for a 2 out of 3. Malt flavor is nice with a slightly bitter finish. I wonder if this Oktoberfest might taste better warm vs cold. Seems the cold may dull the flavor. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Wonderful orange unfiltered color. Sweet hoppy aroma. Light fruits. Nice head.

Love the aroma of roasted barley in this. Dark, rich amber color. Taste of barley not bad, but a little lighter taste than expected. Slight bitter finish. Would pair perfect with brats and other German meats.

Real nice orange amber autumn color and good foamy pour. Aroma is mild. Tastes of nuts and caramel. Tastes great in a cold mug.

beer_brewer_name: The Traveler Beer Company (formerly House Of Shandy)
review_blob:
Nice caramel color, almost like an apple cider. Very flavorful with tastes of apple spice, caramel, cinnamon, and of course pumpkin. Well blended; none of the flavors overpowered the others. Terrific palate with refreshing carbonation. Excellent choice for a warmer fall day and holidays.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Honey and spice aroma. Wonderful rich honey brown color, but not much head off the pour. Complex flavors of honey, lemon, and spices. A little bitter at the end, but nice on the palate. At 11.5%, this brew packs a punch, and you can taste it as you sip. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Boulder Beer A Honey of a Saison

review_blob:
Nice golden full body. Head hung around for several minutes kind of like a milkshake topped with whipped cream. Excellent palate, right amount of carbonation and smooth finish. Tastes of light nut, honey, and flowers. I'm normally not a big Pilsner fan but this would be my choice.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Oskar Blues Mamas Little Yella Pils

review_blob:
Seriously wondering if I got a bad one of the bunch. Given the average overall rating by other reviews, I have to believe I got a skunked bottle. Tasted terrible. Very sour and tasted like aluminum. I'll have to buy this from another store and give it another go. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Not a bad Hefe, but a little too light on the palate. Makes for a nice cold beer on hot summer days. Yellow color is too clear for a Hefe, but for the price it's not bad. The touch of lemon with wheat is good.

Nice amber appearance. Decent head off the pour. The banana notes are there but subtle. Just a personal preference, but would like this beer a bit sweeter to match its name. Good flavor though for someone who prefers just a touch of a special flavor. 
Beer was a tad flat, but I could blame my local liquor store. I can't always trust that their "cold beer" section hasn't been skunked somewhere along its journey. :)
